        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Hereditary isolated aplastic anemia is a rare genetic constitutional aplastic anemia disorder characterized by severe peripheral blood pancytopenia and bone marrow hypoplasia in multiple individuals of a family in the absence of any somatic symptoms. Abnormal bleeding as well as erythrocyte macrocytosis is reported and patients usually become transfusion-dependent."
        },
